cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this replication package, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "Replication Package: Do Health Policy Conclusions Survive Modern DiD? Re-estimating TWFE Studies"
abstract: >
  Replication package for a Master's dissertation that reanalyzes 56 published
  health-economics papers that used Two-Way Fixed Effects (TWFE)
  difference-in-differences, applying modern robust estimators: Callaway-Sant'Anna
  (CS-DID), Sun-Abraham, Borusyak-Jaravel-Spiess (BJS imputation), Bacon
  decomposition, and HonestDiD sensitivity analysis.
authors:
